"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806136","Home Office","false","2017-12-20","<p>The new National Economic Crime Centre has £6m in funding allocated to it in the 18/19 financial year. <br> <br>The Home Office is working with partners across government, law enforcement, regulators and the private sector on the design of the National Economic Crime Centre. It is too early in the design and build process to confirm final staffing numbers.</p><p>Home Office and law enforcement agencies are working together to determine the size of the team that will lead the work to use the power in the Criminal Finances Act 2017 to forfeit criminal money held in suspended bank accounts. We have not yet determined the exact size of that team.</p><p>Decisions on the overall funding of the SFO, NCA and other law enforcement agencies is agreed through the Spending Review process.</p><p>The inaugural meeting of the Economic Crime Strategic Board will take place in the first quarter of 2018.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","119333 ; 119334 ; 119336 ; 119392","2017-12-20T15:47:47.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806136/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806136/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806136/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-13","Fraud","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the written ministerial statement of 11 December on Economic crime and anti-corruption, HCWS329, how many people will be employed in the team dedicated to use the power in the Criminal Finances Act 2017 to forfeit criminal money held in suspended bank accounts.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","119337"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806137","House of Commons Commission","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Serjeant at Arms Office does receive emails and phone calls on the subject of failure to wear a Security Pass but the Office does not make a record of these or hold statistics.</p>","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake",,"2017-12-21T11:49:17.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806137/answer","Biography information for Tom Brake","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806137/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806137/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2017-12-13","House of Commons: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Carshalton and Wallington, representing the House of Commons Commission, how many (a) members, (b) members' staff and (c) other pass holders have been reported to the Serjeant at Arms by security officers or police officers for failure to wear or failure to present on request their Palace of Westminster Security Pass in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","119338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806138","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-18","<p>Requirements for the recruitment and employment of pilots is for industry to determine against their business models and market needs.</p><p> </p><p>The Department of Transport works closely with the aviation industry to ensure it continues to be a major, economic success story for Britain. This includes on issues such as skills and employment, which are topics we are actively exploring as part of our developing Aviation Strategy.</p><p> </p><p>Investment in apprenticeships is one way to insure against a future STEM shortage. The aviation industry has taken the opportunity provided by the introduction of the apprenticeship levy to work together to develop more apprenticeship standards.</p><p> </p><p>The Year of Engineering aims to showcase and celebrate the contribution that engineering makes to today’s world by developing and promoting direct and inspiring experiences of modern engineering throughout 2018. A number of aviation companies have already signed up as Year of Engineering partners to share what they do and I would encourage more to follow and help us reach the target of a million direct experiences for young people, their families and teachers.</p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-12-18T16:02:41.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806138/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806138/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806138/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-13","Aviation: Crew","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the number of professional pilots the UK aviation industry will need by 2030; and what steps he is taking to meet that demand.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","119339"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806139","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-01-03","<p>Defra Ministers were first alerted to China’s proposed import restrictions in July 2017. At Ministers’ request, Defra officials engaged with officials from the Department for International Trade and the Environment Agency over the summer and held meetings with industry in September to discuss the potential impacts of the restrictions.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-01-03T12:46:16.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806139/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806139/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806139/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-13","Waste: China","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when he was first informed of the Chinese notification to the WTO of 18 July 2017 of its restrictions on imports of waste.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","119340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806140","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-20","<p>All taxes remain under review and future decisions on VAT will be continue to be taken as part of the normal Budget process following the UK’s departure from the European Union. In the meantime, the UK remains a member of the EU and will continue to meet its rights and obligations. That includes the application of EU VAT rules.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-12-20T16:35:39.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806140/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806140/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806140/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-13","Charities: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of opportunities to reform the VAT system to support the charity sector following the UK’s departure from the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr David Jones","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","119341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806141","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-12-21","<p>Details of ministerial and senior official meetings are published in the Department’s Quarterly Transparency Returns, which are made publicly available on<a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank"> GOV.UK</a>.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker","118948 ; 118951 ; 118954 ; 118958 ; 118972 ; 118986 ; 118993 ; 119043 ; 119051 ; 119349 ; 119359 ; 119369 ; 119375","2017-12-21T13:24:26.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806141/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806141/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806141/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-12-13","Broadcasting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, with reference to his Department's publication Ministerial Meeting: January to March 2017, if he will publish the names of the attendees at the Broadcasting roundtable attended by Robin Walker MP in March 2017.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806142","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-22","<p>Neither my Rt hon Friend the Secretary of State, nor I have had discussions with charities about the impact of these rules on their work.</p><p>The State aid rules apply to funding given to charities, as they would for any other body, where they are involved in economic activities. The rules are blind as to legal form; rather they are concerned with whether an entity is undertaking economic activities. And equally State aid may be granted legally to charities on the same terms as anyone else if it complies with the rules.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-22T15:12:22.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806142/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806142/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806142/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-13","Charities: Government Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent discussions he has had with charities to discuss the impact of state aid rules on their work.","false","Biography information for Mr David Jones","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","119343"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806143","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-20","<p>Relief for first time buyers is available for shared ownership schemes in respect of the grant of a shared ownership lease on which the buyer has opted to be taxed on the market value of the property.</p><p>Where market value treatment does not apply or has not been opted for, relief for first time buyers is not available in respect of shared ownership schemes.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-12-20T17:15:41.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806143/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806143/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806143/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-13","First Time Buyers: Stamp Duty Land Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether first time buyers on Share to Buy schemes can access the reduction in stamp duty announced in the Autumn Budget 2017.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","119344"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806144","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-22","<p>The Government is aware that the EU negotiating mandate explicitly refers to state aid in the context of any future trade agreement between the EU and UK. This future relationship is subject to negotiation.</p><p> </p><p>While the Government cannot speculate on outcomes at this stage, any future regime will be based on the principles of open and fair markets. As my Right Hon Friend the Prime Minister said in Florence the Government believes “it would be a serious mistake to try to beat other countries’ industries by unfairly subsidising one’s own”.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-22T14:26:56.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806144/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806144/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806144/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-13","Government Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy,what assessment he has  made of the opportunities to reform state aid following the UK’s departure from the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr David Jones","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","119345"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806145","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-18","<p>The information requested is not available.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-12-18T17:21:28.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806145/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806145/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806145/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-13","Housing Benefit: Refuges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate his Department has made of the total (a) weekly and (b) annual housing benefit spend for claimants living within refuge accommodation.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","119346"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806146","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-20","<p>According to published figures, as of 30 September 2017 there were 254 Muslim women in prison.</p><p> </p><p>This is the closest published data to the requested date. We publish end of month prison population figures broken down by religion and sex quarterly, and the statistics can be accessed here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/prison-population-figures-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/prison-population-figures-2017</a>.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-12-20T11:16:42.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806146/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806146/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806146/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-13","Prisoners: Muslims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the number of women of Muslim faith in prison on 1 October 2017.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","119347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806147","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-19","<p>The current public procurement rules will continue to apply until the UK has left the EU following the successful conclusion of exit negotiations. The longer-term opportunities for our procurement regulations are being considered carefully.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-12-19T15:44:13.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806147/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806147/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806147/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-13","Public Sector: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office,what assessment he has made of the opportunities to increase social value in public procurement following the UK’s departure from the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr David Jones","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","119348"
