"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806155","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-18"," The government gave Ofcom powers, through the Digital Economy Act 2017, to publish criteria for children's programmes and, where appropriate, to set conditions on licensed public service channels to ensure that children’s programming meets the criteria. On 29 November Ofcom launched a Review of Children's Content and have invited initial input to the review by 31 January 2018. It intends to publish its findings, alongside any proposed regulatory measures, in summer 2018. ","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-12-18T11:23:25.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806155/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806155/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806155/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-13","Broadcasting Programmes: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what progress she has made on implementing the provision in the Digital Economy Act 2017 on introducing a new Ofcom power on public service broadcasting criteria for the commissioning of children’s content; and what the timetable is for the formal stakeholder consultation to begin.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","119356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806156","Department for Education","false","2017-12-18","<p>The Department for Education published an academy trust survey research report in July 2017. The survey found that the average top slice in a multi academy trust was 4.6%. More detail on the range of top-slicing approaches can be found in the report at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/629779/Academy_Trust_Survey_2017.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/629779/Academy_Trust_Survey_2017.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The amount of any top slice is a matter for the academy trust and will usually depend on the range of central services offered.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","119358","2017-12-18T17:11:21.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806156/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806156/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806156/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-13","Academies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment she has made of the (a) average, (b) highest and (c) lowest amount of annual levy paid by a school to its multi academy trust (i) in total, (ii) for operating costs, (iii) for school improvement and (iv) for efficiency savings.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","119357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806157","Department for Education","false","2017-12-18","<p>The Department for Education published an academy trust survey research report in July 2017. The survey found that the average top slice in a multi academy trust was 4.6%. More detail on the range of top-slicing approaches can be found in the report at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/629779/Academy_Trust_Survey_2017.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/629779/Academy_Trust_Survey_2017.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The amount of any top slice is a matter for the academy trust and will usually depend on the range of central services offered.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","119357","2017-12-18T17:11:21.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806157/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806157/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806157/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-13","Academies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the maximum levy is a multi academy trust can require from a school to operate that multi academy trust.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","119358"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806158","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-12-21","<p>Details of ministerial and senior official meetings are published in the Department’s Quarterly Transparency Returns, which are made publicly available on<a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank"> GOV.UK</a>.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker","118948 ; 118951 ; 118954 ; 118958 ; 118972 ; 118986 ; 118993 ; 119043 ; 119051 ; 119342 ; 119349 ; 119369 ; 119375","2017-12-21T13:24:26.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806158/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806158/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806158/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-12-13","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, with reference to his Department's transparency release entitled Ministerial meetings January to March 2017, who was present at the asset management roundtable attended by his Department's Under-secretary of State, the hon. Member for Worcester, in March 2017.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806159","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-21","<p>The UK routinely trains members of the Indonesian National Police, including Densus 88, across a broad spectrum of subjects at the Jakarta Centre for Law Enforcement Cooperation (JCLEC). Courses are subject to an Overseas Security and Justice Assessment which considers the risk that training might assist participants in violating human rights in the future. No courses at JCLEC offer lethal force training and all UK courses have an element of human rights awareness.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-12-21T13:47:33.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806159/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806159/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806159/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-13","Papua: Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what undertakings were given to the Government that British-trained officers from Detachment 88 would not be deployed for counter-insurgency and political work in West Papua.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","119360"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806160","Department of Health","false","2017-12-18","<p>The Department does not hold information on the numbers of people who have received counselling or other treatment for an addiction to gambling in 2010 to 2017.</p><p> </p><p>Problem gamblers can access services in primary care and secondary care including specialised mental health and addiction services. Any decisions on the commissioning of effective treatment services are the responsibility of local commissioners, based on an assessment of local need.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-12-18T17:44:31.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806160/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806160/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806160/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Gambling: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what information his Department holds on the number of people between the age of 16 and 21 who were receiving treatment for gambling addiction in (a) 2010 and (b) 2017 to date.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","119361"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806161","Department of Health","false","2017-12-18","<p>Since 2012, there have been 37 instances of trusts entering Special Measures for Quality and 14 instances of trusts entering Special Measures for Finance.</p><p> </p><p>As of 15 December 2017, there are 16 trusts in Special Measures for Quality; of which five are foundation trusts and 11 are National Health Service trusts. There have been 21 instances of trusts exiting Special Measures for Quality; of which 13 are foundation trusts and eight are NHS trusts. This includes three trusts that have subsequently re-entered Special Measures for Quality; of which two are foundation trusts and one is an NHS trust.</p><p> </p><p>As of 15 December 2017, there are 11 trusts in Special Measures for Finance; of which five are foundation trusts and six are NHS trusts. Three trusts have exited Special Measures for Finance; of which one is a foundation trust and two are NHS trusts.</p><p> </p><p>Information regarding special measures is published on NHS Improvement’s website.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-12-18T16:32:05.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806161/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806161/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806161/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","NHS: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many (a) NHS trusts and (b) Foundation Trusts have been placed in (i) special measures and (ii) financial special measures in each year since 2012; how many of those Trusts remain in special measures, and if he will publish that information.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","119362"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806162","Department of Health","false","2017-12-18","<p>The Government remains committed to meeting the goals set out in NHS England’s Five Year Forward View for Mental Health and accompanying implementation plan. However, as set out in Implementing the Five Year Forward View for Mental Health, the target of 35% of children with a diagnosable mental health condition receiving treatment by 2020/21 will be reviewed in 2018 following publication of a new national prevalence study.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-12-18T17:08:29.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806162/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806162/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806162/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to his Department's publication Future in Mind, published in March 2015, whether his Department has plans to review the target for 35 per cent of children with diagnosable mental health conditions to receive treatment by 2020-21 as a result of the publication of the green paper, Transforming children and young people’s mental health provision.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","119363"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806163","Department of Health","false","2017-12-18","<p>The Department has no such plans.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not generally ringfence budgets within the National Health Service. Clinicians in clinical commissioning groups (CCGs), who know their patients, have the autonomy to make decisions about the health services that best meet the health needs of their local population. They do this based on patient needs and clinical evidence.</p><p> </p><p>The NHS Operational Planning and Contracting Guidance applies to CCGs and sets out specific requirements, including commissioning mental health services that meet the needs of local populations. This guidance also requires CCGs and NHS England specialised commissioning hubs to increase their spend on mental health services by a greater amount than the growth in their overall programme allocation.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-12-18T16:58:23.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806163/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806163/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806163/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether his Department intends to ringfence mental health budgets in the NHS.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","119364"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806164","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>The number of staff who will form the Mental Health Support Teams as announced in our recent green paper, Transforming Children and Young People’s Mental Health Provision, will be determined according to local circumstances, and will be informed through responses to the Green Paper consultation and tested by initial trailblazer sites.</p><p> </p><p>The trailblazers may take different approaches in each area depending on local need and we will use the trailblazers to test and evaluate different models to inform ongoing roll-out.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-12-21T15:55:54.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806164/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806164/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806164/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Mental Health Services: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many members of staff he plans to recruit to the proposed Mental Health Support Teams.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","119365"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806165","Women and Equalities","false","2017-12-18","<p>The government is aiming to carry out a consultation on the Gender Recognition Act to look at making the process of legally changing gender less bureaucratic and intrusive for transgender people.</p><p>Ahead of the consultation launch, we have been engaging with a range of stakeholders, including women’s refuges, women’s rights charities and trans rights charities to help inform the development of the consultation document.</p><p>We will also encourage women’s refuges, women’s rights charities and trans rights charities to respond to the consultation when it is launched.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-12-18T17:51:47.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806165/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806165/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806165/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-12-13","Gender Recognition Act 2004","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, whether her Department plans to consult (a) Women's refuges (b) women's rights charities and (c) trans rights charities ahead of bringing forward legislative proposals to reform the Gender Recognition Act 2004.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","119366"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806166","Department of Health","false","2017-12-18","<p>Since 2014, Public Health England has an on-going contractual relationship with the Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation (IHME) to provide data and quality assure the modelling work undertaken by IHME.</p><p> </p><p>The Global Burden of Disease study (GBD) 2013 findings were published in a series of papers on subjects such as: smoking; overweight and obesity; HIV/AIDS, malaria, and tuberculosis; disability-adjusted life years, and risk factors. The papers are available at:</p><p><a href="http://www.thelancet.com/gbd/2013" target="_blank">http://www.thelancet.com/gbd/2013</a></p><p>Starting with GBD 2015, annual updates of GBD estimates are being produced to provide policymakers, donors, and other decision-makers with the most timely and useful picture of population health. GBD 2015 findings have been published in a series of papers and reports and can be found here:</p><p><a href="http://www.healthdata.org/gbd/publications" target="_blank">http://www.healthdata.org/gbd/publications</a></p><p>GBD collaborators are currently at work on the next update.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-12-18T17:42:42.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806166/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806166/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806166/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many analyses have been jointly undertaken by (a) the NHS, (b) his Department and (c) Public Health England with the (i) Global Burden of Disease or (ii) Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation in each of the last five years; and if he will place copies of any published reports of those studies in the Library.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","119367"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806167","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-18","A list of individuals and organisations that submitted evidence, events attended and other evidence will be published as part of the review.","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-12-18T11:21:39.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806167/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806167/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806167/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-13","S4C Independent Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 13 December 2017 to Question 118314, on S4C Independent Review, whether the list of all parties consulted will include all those who were invited to submit evidence.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","119368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806168","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-12-21","<p>Details of ministerial and senior official meetings are published in the Department’s Quarterly Transparency Returns, which are made publicly available on<a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank"> GOV.UK</a>.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker","118948 ; 118951 ; 118954 ; 118958 ; 118972 ; 118986 ; 118993 ; 119043 ; 119051 ; 119342 ; 119349 ; 119359 ; 119375","2017-12-21T13:24:26.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806168/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806168/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806168/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-12-13","Foreign Investment in UK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, with reference to his Department's transparency release entitled Ministerial meetings January to March 2017, who was present at the Inward Investor roundtable attended by his Department's Under-secretary of State, the hon. Member for Worcester, in February 2017.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119369"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806169","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-18","<p>The Government is working closely with Member States and our partners in the EU institutions to negotiate the best deal for the UK and the EU. It has held discussions with the EU on the future rights of UK nationals and EU27 citizens who currently rely on the Mutual Recognition of Professional Qualifications Directive (2005/36/EC) to have their qualifications recognised after the UK leaves the EU. The results of these discussions are set out in the joint report published by the UK and EU negotiators following Phase 1 of negotiations<sup><sup>[1]</sup></sup>.</p><p> </p><p>[1] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/665869/Joint_report_on_progress_during_phase_1_of_negotiations_under_Article_50_TEU_on_the_United_Kingdom_s_orderly_withdrawal_from_the_European_Union.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/665869/Joint_report_on_progress_during_phase_1_of_negotiations_under_Article_50_TEU_on_the_United_Kingdom_s_orderly_withdrawal_from_the_European_Union.pdf</a></p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-18T16:08:46.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806169/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806169/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806169/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-13","Architecture: Qualifications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent discussions he has had with his EU counterparts on mutual recognition of architects' professional qualifications, set out in EU Directive 2005/36/EC, after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","119370"
