"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806241","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-22","<p>The Office for National Statistics monitors and reports on loneliness and social isolation. Most recently it has published estimates of loneliness nationally in 'Life in the UK' and regionally in 'Social Capital in the UK'. Small sample sizes make it difficult to publish estimates for local authorities. I refer my Hon Friend to the response published by the UK Statistics Authority in response to a question earlier this year. The response can be found at: http <a href="http://qna.files.parliament.uk/qna-attachments/794094/original/PQ115182.pdf" target="_blank">http://qna.files.parliament.uk/qna-attachments/794094/original/PQ115182.pdf</a></p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-12-22T14:30:47.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806241/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806241/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-13","Loneliness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate his Department has made of the number of people affected by loneliness in 2016/17; and if his Department will publish such statistics for each local authority in 2016/17.","false","Biography information for Damien Moore","Southport","Damien Moore","119433"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806242","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-20","<p>We have always been clear that we will roll out Universal Credit in a way that allows us to continue to make improvements.</p><p> </p><p>To accommodate the Universal Credit measures announced in the Budget, we have modified the rollout schedule to ensure we continue to implement this important welfare reform safely and gradually</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-12-20T15:47:08.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806242/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806242/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-13","Universal Credit: Glasgow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, for what reasons the universal credit full service roll-out to Shettleston Jobcentre has been moved back to December 2018.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","119434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806243","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-20","<p>The information is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-12-20T15:45:39.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806243/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806243/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806243/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-13","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 8 November 2017 to Question 110869, if he will make it his policy to regularly publish data on universal credit advances by parliamentary constituency.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","119435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806245","Department of Health","false","2017-12-18","<p>In its Stepping forward to 20/21: Mental Health Workforce Plan for England, Health Education England reported that 194,000 people were employed by the National Health Service providing care for people who need mental health services in 2016. The workforce plan for England envisages the total number of NHS staff employed in mental health will rise to 213,000 in 2020, an increase of 19,000.</p><p> </p><p>Stepping forward to 2020/21: The mental health workforce plan for England is available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.hee.nhs.uk/sites/default/files/documents/CCS0717505185-1_FYFV%20Mental%20health%20workforce%20plan%20for%20England_v5%283%29.pdf" target="_blank">www.hee.nhs.uk/sites/default/files/documents/CCS0717505185-1_FYFV%20Mental%20health%20workforce%20plan%20for%20England_v5%283%29.pdf</a></p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-12-18T17:14:43.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806245/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806245/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806245/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Mental Health Services: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many NHS mental health staff there were in the most recent period for which figures are available; and how many such staff he estimates there will be in 2020.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","119437"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806249","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-10","<p><em>Cabinet Office does not maintain a central database of all regulations made and repealed. All secondary legislation is available at <a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.legislation.gov.uk</a> . The regular business impact target reports available on <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">gov.uk</a> include details of the regulatory provisions that have come into force or ceased to be in force.</em></p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington","119446 ; 119447","2018-01-10T15:19:43.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806249/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806249/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-13","Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many regulations have been repealed since July 2014.","false","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","119441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806251","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Department has not undertaken a formal impact assessment on the potential cost of eliminating or reducing prescription charges for people with long-term medical conditions not already covered by a medical exemption. However, the Prescription Charges Review (the Review) undertaken by Professor Sir Ian Gilmore on behalf of the Department, and published in 2010, estimated that extending exemption, at that time, to all those with a long-term condition would lead to a loss in revenue of between £360 and £430 million. This document is publicly available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/prescription-charges-review-the-gilmore-report" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/prescription-charges-review-the-gilmore-report</a></p><p>The Review does not make specific reference to sufferers of lupus, however, the All Party Parliamentary Group on Sickle Cell and Thalassaemia and the Sickle Cell Society provided written evidence to the Review.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-12-21T16:35:51.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806251/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806251/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Prescriptions: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when the last impact assessment was undertaken of the prescription charge medical exemption list; if he will publish that impact assessment; and whether that impact assessment makes reference to the disproportionate effect on certain groups of Sickle Cell or Lupus.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","119443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806252","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-20","<p>The target to deliver £10 billion of savings only applied in respect of the last Parliament, which was originally expected to run for five years from 2015 to 2020. The Government is currently considering its approach to setting a Business Impact Target in respect of the current Parliament.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-20T15:57:56.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806252/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806252/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-13","Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, when he expects the Government to achieve its target to cut £10 billion of red tape.","false","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","119444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806253","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-19","<p>Information relating to the proceedings of Cabinet Committees, including when and how often they meet, is not disclosed as to do so could harm the frankness and candour of internal discussion. A full list of the Cabinet Committees and Implementation Task Forces, with their membership and terms of reference, can be found on the Cabinet Office's webpage:</p><p> </p><p><em><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-cabinet-committees-system-and-list-of-cabinet-committees" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-cabinet-committees-system-and-list-of-cabinet-committees</a></em></p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2017-12-19T15:31:11.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806253/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806253/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-13","Cabinet Committees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many meetings of the Reducing Regulation sub-Committee have taken place since June 2016.","false","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","119445"
