"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806258","Department of Health","false","2017-12-19","<p>We do not keep a central record of all regulations introduced or repealed by the Department and to obtain that information would incur a disproportionate cost.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","119451","2017-12-19T15:39:59.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806258/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806258/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Department of Health: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many regulations were introduced by the Department for Health in calendar years 2014, 2015 and 2016.","false","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","119450"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806259","Department of Health","false","2017-12-19","<p>We do not keep a central record of all regulations introduced or repealed by the Department and to obtain that information would incur a disproportionate cost.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","119450","2017-12-19T15:39:59.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806259/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806259/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Department of Health: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many regulations were repealed by the Department for Health in calendar years 2014, 2015 and 2016.","false","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","119451"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806260","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-20","<p>Details of the savings to business that were delivered through improvements to regulation during the 2010-15 Parliament are set out in <em>The</em> <em>Ninth Statement of New Regulation, </em>published in December 2014. It is available on <a href="http://www.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.gov.uk</a>.</p><p>The Government has not yet published its final report on the savings to business delivered during the 2015-17 Parliament, but we will do so in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-20T15:57:25.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806260/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806260/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806260/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-13","Business: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will estimate the savings to businesses of the repeal of regulations in 2014, 2015 and 2016.","false","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","119452"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806261","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>No assessment has been made on the potential effect of Minimum Unit Pricing (MUP) in England on the number of children living with an alcohol dependent parent. MUP and its effects will continue to remain under review pending the impact of its implementation in Scotland.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-12-21T17:04:06.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806261/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806261/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806261/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Alcoholic Drinks: Minimum Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of the potential effect of minimum unit pricing in England on the number of children living with an alcohol dependent parent.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","119453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806262","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-20","<p>The Government no longer publishes a statement of new regulations every six months. Under the Small Business, Enterprise and Employment Act 2015, the Government is required to publish an annual report that among other things lists all measures’ impact on business or voluntary bodies, which came into force in the preceding year. The final report for the 2015-17 Parliament will be published in due course.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-20T15:57:01.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806262/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806262/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806262/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-13","Business: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business Energy and Industrial Strategy, when he next plans to publish a list of new UK and EU business regulations that will come into force in the next six months.","false","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","119454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806264","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-20","<p>We are undertaking a comprehensive programme of analytical work looking at the implications of the UK’s withdrawal from the EU. The Government is examining all areas of the UK economy and seeking input from a wide range of businesses and industry bodies in order to inform our negotiations with the EU. Our department works closely with the Department for Exiting the European Union to ensure that they are informed of our understanding of these issues.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-12-20T12:26:16.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806264/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806264/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806264/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-13","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether her Department has established a market access commission on the implications of the withdrawal of the UK from the EU.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","119456"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806265","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-20","<p>Department officials meet regularly with PIP Assessment Providers to discuss all aspects of their delivery of PIP assessments, including ensuring it works effectively for people with long-term health conditions or disabilities.</p><p> </p><p>PIP is a functional assessment, and addresses the impact of an individual’s medical conditions on their daily life, rather than the medical conditions themselves. There is no requirement for the Health Professional to diagnose a condition or to recommend treatment options.</p><p> </p><p>The assessments are undertaken by qualified Health Professionals who are experts in disability analysis with knowledge of the likely functional effects of a wide range of health conditions. They have access to a range of resources as well as experienced clinicians to support them in assessing claimants.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","119458 ; 119459 ; 119461","2017-12-20T15:29:34.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806265/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806265/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806265/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-13","Personal Independence Payment: Autoimmune Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent discussions he has had with Capita on improving that company's management of personal independent payment assessments for people with an auto-immune disease.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","119457"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806266","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-20","<p>Department officials meet regularly with PIP Assessment Providers to discuss all aspects of their delivery of PIP assessments, including ensuring it works effectively for people with long-term health conditions or disabilities.</p><p> </p><p>PIP is a functional assessment, and addresses the impact of an individual’s medical conditions on their daily life, rather than the medical conditions themselves. There is no requirement for the Health Professional to diagnose a condition or to recommend treatment options.</p><p> </p><p>The assessments are undertaken by qualified Health Professionals who are experts in disability analysis with knowledge of the likely functional effects of a wide range of health conditions. They have access to a range of resources as well as experienced clinicians to support them in assessing claimants.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","119457 ; 119459 ; 119461","2017-12-20T15:29:34.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806266/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806266/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806266/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-13","Personal Independence Payment: Blood Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent discussions he has had with Capita on improving that company's management of personal independent payment assessments for people with an  a haematological disease.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","119458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806267","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-20","<p>Department officials meet regularly with PIP Assessment Providers to discuss all aspects of their delivery of PIP assessments, including ensuring it works effectively for people with long-term health conditions or disabilities.</p><p> </p><p>PIP is a functional assessment, and addresses the impact of an individual’s medical conditions on their daily life, rather than the medical conditions themselves. There is no requirement for the Health Professional to diagnose a condition or to recommend treatment options.</p><p> </p><p>The assessments are undertaken by qualified Health Professionals who are experts in disability analysis with knowledge of the likely functional effects of a wide range of health conditions. They have access to a range of resources as well as experienced clinicians to support them in assessing claimants.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","119457 ; 119458 ; 119461","2017-12-20T15:29:34.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806267/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806267/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806267/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-13","Personal Independence Payment: Infectious Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent discussions he has had with Atos on improving that company's management of personal independent payment assessments for people with an infectious disease.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","119459"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806268","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-20","<p>BEIS was created in July 2016. The data incidents recorded and those reported to ICO for BEIS since its creation are:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Date</p></td><td><p>Recorded incidents</p></td><td><p>Reported to ICO</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-20T15:07:36.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806268/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806268/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806268/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-13","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119460"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806269","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-20","<p>Department officials meet regularly with PIP Assessment Providers to discuss all aspects of their delivery of PIP assessments, including ensuring it works effectively for people with long-term health conditions or disabilities.</p><p> </p><p>PIP is a functional assessment, and addresses the impact of an individual’s medical conditions on their daily life, rather than the medical conditions themselves. There is no requirement for the Health Professional to diagnose a condition or to recommend treatment options.</p><p> </p><p>The assessments are undertaken by qualified Health Professionals who are experts in disability analysis with knowledge of the likely functional effects of a wide range of health conditions. They have access to a range of resources as well as experienced clinicians to support them in assessing claimants.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","119457 ; 119458 ; 119459","2017-12-20T15:29:34.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806269/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806269/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806269/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-13","Personal Independence Payment: Autoimmune Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent discussions he has had with Atos on improving that company's management of personal independent payment assessments for people with an auto-immune disease.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","119461"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806270","Attorney General","false","2018-01-03","<p>Neither the AGO or HMCPSI recorded any data incidents in 2015-16 or 2016-17.</p><p>The CPS recorded 183 data incidents in 2015-16 and 242 in 2016-17. Three of the incidents in 2015-16 were referred to the ICO and seven of the incidents in 2016-17.</p><p>The SFO recorded nine data incidents in 2015-16 and 17 in 2016-17. None of these were deemed serious enough to require reporting to the ICO.</p><p>The GLD recorded 63 security incidents in 2015-16 and 45 in 2016-17. None of the incidents in 2015-16 was deemed serious enough to require reporting to the ICO; one was reported to the ICO in 2016-17. The GLD does not specifically record ‘data incidents’ as a reporting category; the figures for ‘security incidents’ include physical and personal security, as well as information security.</p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2018-01-03T16:39:14.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806270/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806270/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806270/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-12-13","Attorney General: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119462"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806271","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-19","<p>Currently there is no legal obligation on data controllers to report breaches of security which result in loss, release or corruption of personal data, the Information Commissioner believes serious breaches should be brought to the attention of his Office. It is at the discretion of departments to define serious breaches.</p><p> </p><p>In 2015-2016 the Cabinet Office had 16 data incidents of which 1 required reporting to the Information Commissioner’s Office.</p><p>In 2016-2017 the Cabinet Office had 36 data incidents of which 3 required reporting to the Information Commissioner’s Office.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-12-19T15:45:32.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806271/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806271/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806271/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-13","Cabinet Office: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119463"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806272","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-19","<p>Personal date incidents are recorded in our annual reports, and these can be found on the gov.uk website.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-12-19T14:18:39.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806272/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806272/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806272/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-13","Department for Communities and Local Government: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119464"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806273","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-20","<p>2,519 data incidents were recorded by the Ministry of Defence (MOD) for the period 01 April 2015 - 31 March 2016. One was reported to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO).</p><p>4,034 data incidents were recorded by the MOD for the period 01 April 2016 - 31 March 2017. Three were reported to the ICO.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-12-20T15:20:27.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806273/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806273/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806273/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-13","Ministry of Defence: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119465"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806274","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-01-16","<p>2015/2016 ​incident management records show the Department captured 4 data breaches​,​ 1​ of which ​were​ sufficiently serious to report to the ICO​. This was a loss by a 3rd party supplier working on behalf of the Office of Civil Society (OCS) collecting survey data​.</p><p> </p><p>​In ​2017​ we introduced a more robust method of incident ​reporting​. In 2016/17 the Department captured ​8 data​ breaches​ of which 3 ​were​ reported to the ICO​.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-01-16T14:22:33.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806274/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806274/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806274/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-13","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many data incidents her Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119466"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806275","Department for Education","false","2017-12-22","<p>The department reports data incidents to the Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO) where a large volume of personal data is concerned and there is a real risk of individuals suffering some harm or where smaller amounts of personal data are involved, the release of which could cause a significant risk of individuals suffering substantial detriment, including substantial distress.</p><p>The department publishes, in its annual report and accounts, information about personal data related incidents and provides fuller details about incidents reported to the ICO.</p><p>The department’s annual report and accounts 2015-16 reported five personal data incidents and informed the ICO, on a courtesy basis, about one of these, which did not fall within the criteria for formal reporting. The accounts can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfe-consolidated-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfe-consolidated-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016</a>.</p><p>The department’s annual report and accounts 2016-17 reported three personal data incidents of which one warranted formal reporting to the Information Commissioner’s Office. The accounts can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfe-consolidated-annual-report-and-accounts-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfe-consolidated-annual-report-and-accounts-2016-to-2017</a>.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-22T11:50:58.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806275/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806275/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806275/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-13","Department for Education: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many data incidents her Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119467"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806276","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-22","<p>The information requested can be found in the table below.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Data related incidents</p></td><td><p>33</p></td><td><p>14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Incidents reported to the ICO</p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-12-22T11:16:04.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806276/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806276/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806276/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-13","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806278","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-08","<p>To date, the Department for Exiting the European Union has not had any data security incidents which have involved the release of data or breached data protection rules. Therefore, we have had no incidents that have required reporting to the ICO.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-01-08T15:43:34.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806278/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806278/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806278/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2017-12-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806279","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-21","<p>Information regarding incidents involving the loss or compromise of personal data is published in the Foreign and Commonwealth Office's Annual Report and Accounts.</p><p>The figures concerned are on page 41 of the 2017 report and page 54 of the 2016 report.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-12-21T11:49:36.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806279/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806279/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806279/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-13","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806280","Women and Equalities","false","2017-12-22","<p>Since becoming part of the Department for Education (DfE) organisational structure in September 2015, information relating to personal data incidents for the Government Equalities Office (GEO) is held by the DfE and is included in the reply given by the Secretary of State for Education to PQ 119467.</p><p>The DfE reports data incidents to the Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO) where a large volume of personal data is concerned and there is a real risk of individuals suffering some harm or where smaller amounts of personal data are involved, the release of which could cause a significant risk of individuals suffering substantial detriment, including substantial distress.</p><p>The DfE publishes, in its annual report and accounts, information about personal data related incidents and provides fuller details about incidents reported to the ICO.</p><p>The department’s annual report and accounts for 2015-16 and 2016-17 report on personal data incidents and incidents that warranted formal reporting to the ICO.</p><p>The accounts can be found at the following links:</p><p>2015-16 - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfe-consolidated-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfe-consolidated-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016</a>.</p><p>2016-17 - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfe-consolidated-annual-report-and-accounts-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfe-consolidated-annual-report-and-accounts-2016-to-2017</a>.</p><p>Of the incidents reported in the periods 2015-16 and 2016-17, none of the DfE’s reported incidents and incidents reported to the ICO related to the GEO.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-22T12:01:01.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806280/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806280/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806280/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-12-13","Government Equalities Office: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, how many data incidents her Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806281","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Department recorded three data incidents in 2015-16 and six in 2016-17. The Department did not report any data incidents to the Information Commissioner’s Office in 2015-16 and 2016-17.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-12-21T16:03:42.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806281/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806281/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806281/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Department of Health: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806282","Home Office","false","2017-12-21","<p>The number of data incidents recorded by the Home Department and reported to the Information Commissioner’s Office, is as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td>YEAR</td><td>TOTAL INCIDENTS RECORDED</td><td>REPORTED TO ICO</td></tr><tr><td>2015-16</td><td>62</td><td>2</td></tr><tr><td>2016-17</td><td>70</td><td>2</td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2017-12-21T17:18:01.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806282/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806282/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806282/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-13","Home Office: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many data incidents her Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806283","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-19","<p>The number of data incidents recorded and reported by DFID to the Information Commissioners’ Office in 2015-16 and 2016-17 is published in DFID’s Annual Report for each of these years. These can be found on GOV.UK at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dfid-annual-report-2011-2012" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dfid-annual-report-2011-2012</a>.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-12-19T14:35:22.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806283/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806283/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806283/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-13","Department for International Development: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many data incidents her Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806284","Department for International Trade","false","2017-12-20","<p>The Department for International Trade (DIT) was formed in 2016. From its creation to 31<sup>st</sup> March 2017, DIT recorded one data incident. It did not contain sufficient personal data to warrant a report to the Information Commissioner’s Office.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-12-20T12:09:38.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806284/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806284/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806284/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-12-13","Department for International Trade: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119476"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806285","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-20","<p>BEIS was created in July 2016. The Senior Information Risk Officer (SIRO) role has not been vacant at any time since the creation of the Department.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-20T15:08:11.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806285/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806285/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806285/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-13","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many times his Department's Senior Information Risk Officer roles been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119477"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806286","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-20","<p>Departments are obligated to publish breaches of personal data in their Annual Reports and Accounts. Copies of the Ministry of Justice’s Annual Report and Accounts, including 2015-16 and 2016-17 and can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/630239/moj-annual-report-2016-17.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/630239/moj-annual-report-2016-17.pdf</a> (pages 34-35)</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministry-of-justice-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministry-of-justice-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016</a> (page 32)</p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice takes any data loss seriously. The Department handles millions of records of personal data and each loss is assessed, including instances of small localised losses, which make up the vast majority of the incidents which occur. The department continues to take steps to address the number of data incidents occurring including staff training and awareness campaigns and a review of the governance structures in place to protect data and information.</p><p> </p><p>In compliance with the requirements of the Cabinet Office Security Policy Framework the Department has had four departmental Senior Information Risk Owners in post since 2012 and there have been no vacancies during that period.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","119499","2017-12-20T11:16:33.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806286/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806286/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806286/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-13","Ministry of Justice: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119478"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806287","Attorney General","false","2018-01-03","<p>In the event of any Senior Information Risk Officer (SIRO) vacancy, a deputy SIRO or appropriate senior individual is appointed to temporarily cover the role.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2018-01-03T16:38:16.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806287/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806287/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806287/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-12-13","Attorney General: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many times the Law Officers' Departments Senior Information Risk Officer roles has been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806288","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-12-21","<p>No data incidents have been recorded or reported to the Information Commissioner’s Office for the years 2015-16 or 2016-17.</p><p> </p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2017-12-21T11:14:34.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806288/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806288/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806288/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-12-13","Northern Ireland Office: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806289","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-19","<p>This information is not available. In the event of a SIRO vacancy, a deputy SIRO or appropriate senior individual is appointed to temporarily cover the role.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-12-19T15:43:21.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806289/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806289/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806289/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-13","Cabinet Office: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many times his Department's Senior Information Risk Officer roles been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806290","Scotland Office","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Scotland Office had no data incidents, either recorded, or reported to the Information Commissioner’s Office, in either 2015-16 or 2016-17.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-12-21T10:54:32.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806290/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806290/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806290/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-12-13","Scotland Office: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806291","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-19","<p>The role has not been vacant at any period of time since 2012.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-12-19T14:17:22.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806291/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806291/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806291/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-13","Department for Communities and Local Government: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many times his Department's Senior Information Risk Officer roles been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119483"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806292","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-21","<p>This response relates to both the central Department and its agencies which includes specifically the Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA), Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA), Maritime and Coastguard Agency (MCA) and Vehicle Certification Agency (VCA).</p><p> </p><p>In 2015-16, 14 data incidents were centrally recorded, with two reported to the Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO). In 2016-17, six were centrally reported, with none reported to the ICO.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-12-21T13:24:49.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806292/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806292/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806292/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-13","Department for Transport: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119484"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806293","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-20","<p>The Ministry of Defence Senior Information Risk Officer role has not been vacant during this period.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-12-20T15:19:54.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806293/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806293/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806293/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-13","Ministry of Defence: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many times his Department's Senior Information Risk Officer role has been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806294","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-21","<p>Since December 2013 this role and responsibility not been vacant at any time. Data before December 2013 is not centrally held.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-12-21T17:12:22.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806294/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806294/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806294/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-13","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many times her Department's Senior Information Risk Officer roles has been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806295","Department for Education","false","2017-12-22","<p>Although records are not kept, we are not aware of any occasion since 2012 when the department’s Senior Information Risk Officer role has not been filled.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-22T12:01:54.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806295/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806295/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806295/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-13","Department for Education: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many times her Department's Senior Information Risk Officer roles been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806296","Wales Office","false","2017-12-18","<p>The Department recorded one data incident in 2015-16 and one in 2016-17. These incidents are disclosed in the Department’s 2015-16 and 2016-17 Annual Reports and Accounts. There have been no incidents reported to the Information Commissioner’s Office.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2017-12-18T13:33:20.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806296/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806296/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806296/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-12-13","Wales Office: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119488"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806297","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-19","<p>The department has had no recorded gaps between the appointments of the 3 SIRO’s that have held the post since 2012.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-12-19T12:09:51.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806297/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806297/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806297/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-13","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many times his Department's Senior Information Risk Officer roles been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806298","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2018-01-03","<p>Since the Formation of the Department - our Senior Information Risk Owner (SIRO) Role has remained filled. At any time that the post has been passed from Senior to Senior, a handover has been completed to ensure that there has been no gap and no loss of continuity.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-01-03T17:54:49.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806298/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806298/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806298/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-12-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many times his Department's Senior Information Risk Officer role has been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806299","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-21","<p>​The Senior Information Risk Officer (SIRO) role has not been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-12-21T11:50:40.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806299/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806299/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806299/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-13","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many times his Department's Senior Information Risk Officer role has been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806300","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-19","<p>DWP publishes details of data incidents and the number of cases recorded and reported to the Information Commissioner’s Office in the Department’s Annual Report and Accounts, available on <a href="http://www.gov.uk" target="_blank"><em>www.gov.uk</em></a>. No incidents were reported in 2015/16 or 2016/17 (as recorded at pages 84 and 92 respectively of the Reports for those years).</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-12-19T12:57:33.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806300/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806300/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806300/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-13","Department for Work and Pensions: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many data incidents his Department (a) recorded and (b) reported to the Information Commissioner's Office in (i) 2015-16 and (ii) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806301","Women and Equalities","false","2017-12-22","<p>As part of the Department for Education organisational structure, the Government Equalities Office (GEO) does not have a Senior Information Risk Officer role but shares that of the Department for Education (DfE). This was also the case when GEO was part of other departments. In September 2012, GEO moved from the Home Office to the Department for Culture, Digital, Media and Sport (DCMS). In September 2015, GEO moved from DCMS to DfE.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-22T11:59:51.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806301/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806301/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806301/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-12-13","Government Equalities Office: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, how many times the Government Equalities Office's Senior Information Risk Officer role has been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806302","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>The responsibilities and functions of the Senior Information Risk Owner have consistently been discharged at Board level within the Department from 2012.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-12-21T16:14:13.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806302/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806302/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806302/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Department of Health: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many times his Department's Senior Information Risk Officer role has been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119494"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806303","Home Office","false","2017-12-21","<p>The position has not been vacant for a week or longer since 2012</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2017-12-21T17:13:57.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806303/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806303/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806303/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-13","Home Office: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many times her Department's Senior Information Risk Officer role has been vacant for a week or longer since 2012.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119495"
