"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805197","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-18","<p>The Interim Report of Dame Judith Hackitt's review into Building Regulations and Fire Safety was laid in Parliament on 18 December. Dame Judith's Final Report is expected to be published in Spring 2018.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-12-18T16:22:05.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805197/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805197/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805197/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-12","Building Regulations and Fire Safety Independent Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will place a copy of the interim report of the Hackitt review of building regulations and fire safety in the Library; and on what date he the final report will be published.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","118869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805198","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-19","<p>Defra has not made a specific assessment of the effect of fly-tipping on wildlife and husbanded animals. The Government is committed to tackling the impact of fly-tipping on wildlife, farmland and local communities.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-12-19T17:26:07.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805198/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805198/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805198/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-12","Fly-tipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on wildlife or husbanded animals of fly tipping?","true","Biography information for Simon Hart","Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire","Simon Hart","118870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805199","Department for Education","false","2017-12-18","<p>Department officials have written to all local councils in England asking them to review whether they commissioned forensic hair strand tests for drug and alcohol use by Trimega Laboratories Limited (Trimega) during the period January 2010 to April 2014, and whether any action is necessary to fulfil their safeguarding responsibilities. We continue to work with local councils to establish the extent to which they used Trimega during this period.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-18T17:22:36.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805199/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805199/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805199/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-12","Trimega","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 11 December 2017 to Question 118056,  what the timetable is for local authorities to report to her Department whether they commissioned forensic hair strand tests for drug and alcohol use from Trimega Laboratories Limited (Trimega) during the period January 2010 to April 2014.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","118871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805200","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-12-18","<p>As outlined in the Government future partnership paper on foreign policy, defence and development, we are open to considering options and models for participation in the European Defence Industrial Development Programme (EDIDP) after we have left the EU. Any decisions on the terms of UK participation in the EDIDP will form part of our wider negotiations.</p><p>We have argued strongly during the current negotiations of the EDIDP draft regulation that it should be open to third country industrial participation, and that it complements other cooperative programmes, including those developed through NATO. The General Affairs Council endorsed its general approach to the draft regulation on 12 December 2017.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-12-18T17:06:47.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805200/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805200/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805200/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-12-12","EU Defence Policy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what representations he has made to the European Commission on UK participation in the European Defence Industrial Development programme.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","118872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805201","Scotland Office","false","2017-12-20","<p>I currently have no plans to visit a food bank in my capacity as Secretary of State for Scotland in January 2018.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-12-20T11:15:32.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805201/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805201/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805201/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-12-12","Food Banks: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, whether he plans to visit a food bank in January 2018.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","118873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805202","Department of Health","false","2017-12-20","<p>It is expected that papers from the project will be submitted by the Small Area Health Statistics Unit to peer reviewed journals in early 2018, and it is likely that the papers will be published a few months after submission.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-12-20T17:19:40.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805202/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805202/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805202/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-12","Incinerators: Health Hazards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, on what date the study on incinerators by the Small Area Health Statistics Unit will be published.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","118874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805203","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-20","<p>With the proposed regulation still subject to EU Council and EU Parliamentary approval, and to be tested in practice in 2019 and 2020, it is too early to draw any substantive assessment of its effects on Departmental policies. To help ensure a positive outcome, our current priorities are: to ensure that the terms of the regulation are flexible enough to attract a wide range of innovative industrial proposals; that while the regulations focus is on encouraging industrial cooperation within the EU it also supports other international cooperation, such as through NATO; and that it allows third country industrial participation. We have also made it known to the EU and our partners that we are open to considering options and models for participation in the European Defence Industrial Development Programme after we have left the EU, though any final decision shall form part of the wider withdrawal negotiations.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-12-20T16:18:31.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805203/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805203/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805203/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-12","EU Defence Policy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the effect on his Department's polices of the proposed European Council and Parliament regulation to establish a European Defence Industrial Development Programme.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","118875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805204","Wales Office","false","2017-12-18","<p>It is not possible to estimate the value of inward investment from the Republic of Ireland to Wales. Both the Department for International Trade (DIT) and the Office for National Statistics (ONS) produce inward investment statistics. DIT’s published data doesn’t connect origin and destination for Foreign Direct Investment (FDI) projects. ONS data meanwhile operates at aggregated national level. The information below shows the value of inward investment from the Republic of Ireland to the UK for each year from 2007 to 2016.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2007</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2008</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2009</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Value (£ million)</p></td><td><p>7,192</p></td><td><p>8,613</p></td><td><p>9,248</p></td><td><p>7,565</p></td><td><p>10,619</p></td><td><p>9,008</p></td><td><p>11,911</p></td><td><p>13,825</p></td><td><p>12,309</p></td><td><p>11,485</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Source: Office for National Statistics</p><p> </p><p>Given the fact that Ireland is Wales’ fourth largest export market and the strong ties between the ports of Fishguard and Rosslare in the south and Holyhead and Dublin in the north, I recognise the key economic links that exist between the two nations.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-12-18T13:24:44.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805204/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805204/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805204/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-12-12","Foreign Investment in UK: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what estimate he has made of the value of inward investment from the Republic of Ireland to Wales in each year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","118876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805205","Home Office","false","2017-12-18","<p>The enforcement of the Hunting Act 2004 is an operational matter for the police. It is for individual Chief Constables to determine how their resources are deployed and it is for locally elected PCCs to hold their forces to account, including on how they tackle the crimes that matter most to residents and businesses in rural and urban areas alike.</p><p>If the police face unexpected or exceptional events, there is an established process by which Police and Crime Commissioners can apply for Special Grant funding to help with these costs.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","118878","2017-12-18T12:36:19.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805205/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805205/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805205/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-12","Hunting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what guidance she has issued to Chief Constables and Police Commissioners on the frequency with which police officers should attend meetings of the local hunt?","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","118877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805206","Home Office","false","2017-12-18","<p>The enforcement of the Hunting Act 2004 is an operational matter for the police. It is for individual Chief Constables to determine how their resources are deployed and it is for locally elected PCCs to hold their forces to account, including on how they tackle the crimes that matter most to residents and businesses in rural and urban areas alike.</p><p>If the police face unexpected or exceptional events, there is an established process by which Police and Crime Commissioners can apply for Special Grant funding to help with these costs.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","118877","2017-12-18T12:36:19.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805206/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805206/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-12","Hunting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to ensure full cost recovery from local hunts for the attendance of police officers at hunts and what discussions she has held with (a) the Association of Chief Police Officers, (b) Chief Constables and (c) Police and Crime Commissioners.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","118878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805207","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-18","<p>Most full time students in higher education do not qualify for benefits or tax credits. Universal Credit is no different, as students, including disabled students and those with health conditions, access fees and living costs to support their higher education courses through various loans and grants funded by the Department for Education.</p><p> </p><p>However, if a person is in receipt of Universal Credit or legacy benefits because of disability or ill health, they are not discouraged from taking up higher education that may help them in the future. If they take up a course and receive a student loan, tuition fees and cost of books are disregarded but maintenance costs are taken into account as student income.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","118880","2017-12-18T17:47:28.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805207/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805207/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-12","Universal Credit: Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the introduction of universal credit on (a) full-time and (b) part-time university students who have a child or children as a (i) lone parent and (ii) couple.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","118879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805208","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-18","<p>Most full time students in higher education do not qualify for benefits or tax credits. Universal Credit is no different, as students, including disabled students and those with health conditions, access fees and living costs to support their higher education courses through various loans and grants funded by the Department for Education.</p><p> </p><p>However, if a person is in receipt of Universal Credit or legacy benefits because of disability or ill health, they are not discouraged from taking up higher education that may help them in the future. If they take up a course and receive a student loan, tuition fees and cost of books are disregarded but maintenance costs are taken into account as student income.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","118879","2017-12-18T17:47:28.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805208/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805208/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805208/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-12","Universal Credit: Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what comparative assessment his Department has made of the effect of (a) the introduction of universal credit and (b) previous benefit systems on (a) full-time and (b) part-time disabled university students.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","118880"
