"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805216","Department of Health","false","2017-12-20","<p>Responsibility for commissioning open access sexual health services is devolved to local authorities through the Health and Social Care Act 2012. Public Health England does not engage in the detailed procurement process of individual services.</p><p> </p><p>Delivery of the London Sexual Health Transformation Programme e-service is the responsibility of local authorities and it is for local authority commissioners to determine the start date for the service and when an evaluation framework will be made available. It is anticipated that the e-service will commence in January 2018.</p><p> </p><p>Where interim service arrangements are required locally ahead of commencement of the e-service they will be agreed and implemented by the relevant local authority. Any cost linked to these interim measures will vary depending on local arrangements.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","118889 ; 118890 ; 118891","2017-12-20T17:30:13.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805216/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805216/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/805216/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-12","Genito-urinary Medicine: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 13 November 2017 to Question 112168, on Genito-urinary Medicine: Greater London, which non-compliance clauses have been triggered by the later than originally planned start date in the e-service contract for the London Sexual Health Transformation Programme .","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","118888"
